node.text:
Kloof House, a short film that explores the idea of indoors and outdoors coexisting. A family home positioned below Lion’s Head, reinforcing the connection to nature and its cycles.
Share this video with someone who needs to see this project!
.

#architecture_hunter 
Accordingly to @omniviewdesign, “the main ambition behind the design of the Villa, was to create a home that combines a strong sense of centricity with flowing connections to its natural environment.

To achieve this, the model of the ancient Greek home was studied carefully as a departure point. In fact, the massing and master planning of spiral Villa Is very close to the ancient Greek home.

The ancient Greek geometry of the spiral has been used to organize and Reinvent this master plan as a sequence of activities. The flow of the spiral represents a spectrum from private to public and ends in the Centrepoint.

There, The Villa features an abstraction or the ancient Greek "Hestia", which in this case is materialized as a central exterior sitting under the shade of an olive tree.

This way the goal of the ancient Greek house to offer privatized exterior space is realized, but at the same time strong relationships to the peripheral functions are created •
.
.
.
.
.

This year, due to the COVID-19 Pandemic, Casacor, an exhibition of architecture, design and decoration that takes place annually in several cities in Brazil and the world, had to be different.

#CasacorJanelas invited several architects and designers to design spaces inside containers, placed in different spots of the city.

In this edition, LG @lgdobrasil proposed Suite Arquitetos @suite_arquitetos to design the “Connected House”, the container located in Praça Cidade de Milão, with landscape designing by Bia Abreu @biaabreu_paisagismo. 

In the kitchen, the architects specified the LG Studio Line appliances, in addition to the Smart LG Side by Side Inverter refrigerator. In the living room, they artistically composed the wall with frames and also with: the LG 65 ”4K OLED HDR Smart TV, awarded as the best TV on the market, the mirrored Artcool air conditioning and the Multi Artcool Gallery.

“LG Connected House” also has other sophisticated products of the brand. Check everything else here: lg.com/br/casa-cor

————

Neste ano, por conta da Pandemia do COVID-19, a Casacor, uma mostra de arquitetura, design e decoração que acontece anualmente em várias cidades do Brasil e do mundo, teve que ser diferente. 

A Casacor Janelas propôs convidar diversos arquitetos e designers para projetarem espaços dentro de containers, espalhados em toda a cidade. 

Nesta edição a LG @lgdobrasil chamou a Suíte Arquitetos @suite_arquitetos para desenhar a “Casa Conectada LG”, cujo container fica na Praça Cidade de Milão, com projeto paisagístico de Bia Abreu @biaabreu_paisagismo. 

Na cozinha, os arquitetos especificaram os eletrodomésticos da Linha Studio LG, além da geladeira Smart LG Side by Side Inverter. 
Já na sala de estar, artisticamente entre os quadros compuseram a parede com: a Smart TV LG 65” 4K OLED HDR, eleita a melhor TV do mercado, o ar condicionado Artcool espelhado e o Multi Artcool Gallery. 

A “Casa Conectada LG” ainda conta com demais sofisticados produtos da marca. Confira tudo aqui: lg.com/br/casa-cor

Dark timber and curved lines 🖤 Send this post to someone who will love this project! 

_project: Round House 
_architecture: @feldmanarchitecture 
_photographer: @adamrousephoto 
_location: South Bay, #California, #USA 

“At Round House, a concentric hallway traces the kitchen, leading to discrete pie-shaped rooms carefully arranged to demarcate private from the public space. An outdoor deck is strategically carved out at the intersection of the living room and kitchen – framing sprawling views of the South Bay. Tall, curved pocket doors vanish into the walls, asserting a seamless indoor-outdoor connection”, say the architects.

_project: MC House
_architecture: @Basiches
_landscape design: @AlexHanazaki
_photographer: @FranParente
_lighting project: @MingroneIluminacao
_location: #SaoPaulo #Brazil

____

_woodworks: @neobambu
_facade’s material: @tresuno_revestimentos
_coating application: @lab88revestimentos
_coating: @colormixrevestimentos

Framed by nature, MC House's project is an ode to minimalism. The architects José Basiches and Ronaldo Shinohara audaciously proposed to coat the 1,800 sqm house in only one finishing: white concrete. The result is a poetic contrast between architecture and the native vegetation that is perfectly integrated to the landscape design proposed by Hanazaki. Another highlight in the project is the elegant lighting design, which makes the house work as a lamp during nights, promoting a refugee in the city to the family who lives there. 

#brazilianarchitecture #landscapedesign #lightingdesign #minimalism #concrete #concretehouse

#architecture_hunter
What is your favorite project featuring @and_light's products? 

Both images 1 and 2 feature lamps designed by @cheintzman. The first one is Vale Wall, a series that aspires to strike a balance between classic utilitarianism and ornate luminaire.

The second one shows the Pipeline series, a linear LED light that has the ability to expand the scale of the fixture, creating an infinite range of tailored lights.

Images 3 and 4's lamps are designed by @lukas_peet. The third one features the Button Pendant. With a wide circular surface LED, 
it casts a warm and inviting light.

And the fourth one features the Pebble Pendant. Sculptural and translucent, two glass-blown shapes come together entering in dialogue. 

Visit & follow @and_light to know more!

How much do you like #minimalism? 

_project: Casa Cielo
_architecture: @hwstudioarq 
_visualization: @bs_arq 
_location: Morelia, #Mexico City 

This bedroom is pure minimalism! No ornaments, only the essentials. Even though the project’s monochromatic palette may make it look cold, the rounded ceiling brings coziness and a welcoming feeling. It also has a futuristic atmosphere! Do you agree? What are your thoughts on it? 

#bedroom #bedroomdesign #mexicandesign #home

_project: Levo’s House
_architecture: @clintonmurray 
_photographer: @peterbbennetts 
_location: Hawthorn, #Australia 

“The design 'moment' for us was taking the planning control stipulating a 'pitched roof' and adapting the triangular geometry of the site into a folded y roof that reads as lightly as possible. We worked closely with an extraordinarily creative (old school!) engineer from Canberra Ken Murtagh to create a roof that mystifies!” say the architects. 

#australiandesign #australianarchitecture #house #home #homedesign

What a lovely project! Describe this living room in ONE word! 

_project: Country Road Residence 
_design: @noasantos 

The abundance of natural light, coming from the floor-to-ceiling-windows, added to the project’s palette composed  of monochromatic tones and organic textures make it a very welcoming space.
